2. cs.LG - The paper uses DBNs, which are a type of deep learning model, for optimization. This falls under the scope of machine learning and specifically, the sub-category of learning theory (LG). 
3. cs.NE - The paper discusses the use of neural networks (DBNs) for optimization, which falls under the scope of neural networks and computational neuroscience (NE). 
4. cs.DM - The paper deals with discrete optimization problems, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms (DM). 
5. cs.PL - The paper discusses the use of inductive logic programming (ILP) for incorporating domain-based background knowledge into the optimization process. This falls under the scope of programming languages and compilers (PL).
